100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 31, 1925, the world was abuzz with the news of the ongoing negotiations for the Locarno Treaties, aimed at ensuring peace in Europe following the devastation of World War I. In the United States, the stock market continued to show signs of optimism, reflecting a booming economy in the Roaring Twenties. Meanwhile, in China, tensions escalated as the Nationalists and Communists clashed, raising concerns over stability in the region.
